## Rules

### BACK-001: Function Length
severity: ERROR
scope: all functions and methods
rule: Functions MUST NOT exceed the configured line limit. Long functions MUST be decomposed into smaller, named functions.
threshold: max_method_lines=30, max_complexity=10
example_correct: |
  def process_order(order: Order) -> Result:
      validated = _validate(order)
      return _save(validated)
example_incorrect: |
  def process_order(order):
      # 80 lines of mixed validation, persistence, and notification...

### BACK-002: Error Handling
severity: ERROR
scope: all service boundaries and I/O operations
rule: All recoverable errors MUST be returned as typed Result values. Raising exceptions for control flow is prohibited. Every I/O call MUST have explicit error handling.
threshold: max_method_lines=30
example_correct: |
  def read_file(path: Path) -> Result[str, str]:
      try:
          return Ok(path.read_text())
      except OSError as exc:
          return Err(f"Cannot read {path}: {exc}")
example_incorrect: |
  def read_file(path: Path) -> str:
      return path.read_text()  # unhandled OSError
